    "post_id": "1595786221594211800",
    "filename": "2017-09-03_1595786221594211743.jpg",
    "description": "What defines your worth? And who gets to define it?\n__________________\n\nI've been feeling very insecure lately, not good enough, not important. I notice it creeping up on me when I see other people do great things and the first thing that pops up in my mind is not \"go you, that's awesome\" but \"does this make me less awesome then\". Ever since recovering from an eating disorder I decided to stop comparing myself to others, now the comparing seems to be creeping back but it's not just about looks anymore, it's about character and talents, and in my opinion that's even worse.\n________________\nI'm striving to be the kind of person that believes in abundance and not scarcity, I strive to be the kind of person that stands firmly into her self, that trusts her gut and her gifts. I'm only human so sometimes I fall into this trap of the mind and the ego but every time I catch myself more easily. I am a wildwoman, I'm only human, I am flawed and awesome and perfect at the same time, just as I'm supposed to be!\n#onlyhuman #keepingitreal #selfworth #comparing #comparison #mind #ego #psychology #patterns #me #beyou #youareworthy #flaws #selflove #selfworth #me #mindful #yoga #wildwoman #fierce #sacredfemininity #witch #truth #introspection #vulberability #authenticity #abundance #raiseyourvibration",
