    "filename": "2018-08-21_1850838250034944078.jpg",
    "description": "As a sensitive person with a sensitive nervous system, part of my practice around boundaries is redefining ‚Äúnormal‚Äù. I remember the doctor saying I would recover in no time because I am a young and healthy individual. News flash, I am not recovering quickly - I might never recover as quickly as other people. And I‚Äôm okay with that. The hard thing is the expectation of ‚Äúnormal‚Äù, of people around you who are moving at a different pace. \n_\nSo I have to set firm boundaries: other people‚Äôs opinions about my recovery are none of my business, putting other people‚Äôs timeline on my body is not helping, pushing myself because I feel like I should is not healing.\n_\nEvery body is different. Read that again and let it sink in. Every. Body. Is. Different. So whenever you feel angry at your body, for not being normal, remember this, this is your pace, your body knows best.\n_\n#yourbodyknowsbest #hsp #sensitivenervoussystem #adrenalfatigue #spoonie #healing #thereisnowrongway #infection #boundaries #redefiningnormal #holistichealth #lifeofanhsp #bunnynervoussystem #recovery #grace #thebodyknows #selfcare",
