    "filename": "2018-12-25_1942030236239466750.jpg",
    "description": "I notice around the holidays that it‚Äôs harder for me to not compare myself to others. I am such a romantic when it comes to Christmas, part of it is personality and part of it is because I want to believe in the dreamy vision of Christmas I see in movies and here on Instagram. \n_\nIn reality I‚Äôm down with a cold, I‚Äôm spending Christmas with just my boyfriend because my family situation is complicated and our Christmas Eve consisted of me dressing up and putting on lipstick, drinking one glass of champagne and then getting a fever, being grumpy, trying not to fall asleep because it‚Äôs Christmas and we are supposed to have fun.\n_\nWhy do I feel the need to share this? Because I have this feeling that I‚Äôm not alone in this, we all crave some magic and perfection from time to time and Christmas seems like the perfect time to create all that. So I‚Äôm inviting you to practice what I am practicing right now: I show myself grace for being hard on myself and comparing myself to others, we all have wounds and we all wish for things and that‚Äôs fine. I practice on finding beauty and gratitude in what is, right now, not in what could be or on what other people have. Where is the beauty in this moment, even if it isn‚Äôt perfect? How can I honour what is, right now?\n_\n#christmas #shadowwork #christmaslights #comparison #findgrace #gratitude #itsokaytonotbeokay #keepingitreal #open #authenticsharing #findbeauty #presence #beherenow #presenceoverperfect #gentlereminder #nowage #consciousliving",
