    "description": "Coming home for me is all about space. Cleaning a space, attuning to a space, taking up space. I always have a hard time switching environments, I‚Äôm the kind of person that hates to leave for a holiday and then hates to come back, over time I found that some actions and rituals help me easy into coming back home and grounding.\n_\nUnpack. Take your time to put all your things back in their right spots and to find a nice space for anything you might have brought along.\n_\nAir. Open windows, let in fresh air, let the rooms breathe and maybe use a palo santo stick or some incense to cleanse and recharge to space.\n_\nTake up space. I love to spend time with my sacred spaces and set up new altars when I get home from a trip. Nurturing my plants and taking some time to dust, vacuum while organising things, it helps me to ground.\n_\nOthers things that really help me to get back into a rhythm when I get home is taking enough time off after a trip to wander around and get used to being home again, starting my first day home off with meditation and a nice, long bath üõÅ \n_\n#consciousliving #home #takeupspace #grounding #travelgram #homecoming #rituals #attuning #createspace #sacredspace #altar #selfcare #travelblues #yoga #holistichealth #air #recharge #ritualbath #hsp #highlysensitive",
