    "filename": "2019-01-26_1965264173531044010.jpg",
    "description": "This morning in class I was talking about how our bodies react best to balance, how it feels safest to follow intense opening with a moment of contraction and softening. Contraction is a natural reaction to expansion, whether it‚Äôs in the body or the mind. Our systems focus on balance, balancing our extreme situations or feelings with a counterpoint. \n_\nI used to look at moments of contraction and falling back into old patterns as a sign of not being on the right track but now I know it‚Äôs exactly the opposite. If you come across resistance and contraction you are definitely on the right track. It‚Äôs a natural reaction from you body and your mind, trying to keep you safe, trying to keep you balanced. There is so much to learn in this space, not running away from the discomfort, not seeing it as a sign to go back to the old but instead learning to see it for what it is, the fact that you are outgrowing an old self, an old way of doing things.\n_\nAnd a special thanks to @wildsoulhealing for blowing my mind when I first heard her talk about contraction/expansion!\n_\n#leanin #contraction #balance #holistichealth #yogatherapy #mindbodysoul #growth #balance #expansion #cyclicalliving #consciousliving #yogini #lifeofayogi #findcomfortinthediscomfort #soften #lightworker #yin #yogaleuven",
