    "description": "Sometimes I get swept up in planning and what other people are doing and what my agenda is telling me I should be doing and it always ends in the same way: me, on the couch or in bed or hiding in some bathroom, in tears. this is a lesson I keep learning, planning is good but no plan can ever be more important than what your body is telling you. When I trust this I get everything done that I want to, in ways that are completely not how I planned them to be, when I sink in to what I need, more action, more rest, more alone time, more time to connect.. and I can let go of the idea that there should be a plan to follow somewhere, I can create magic, even as a highly sensitive person, even as an introvert, even as someone who‚Äôs adrenals aren‚Äôt always all too happy. \n_\n\nTrust me when I say that you don‚Äôt have to keep up with anyone, you can follow your own pace. everyone‚Äôs body is different, everyone‚Äôs nervous system is different, how you are feeling right now could be entirely different from how you will feel tomorrow. Stop thinking in terms of rules and should, make your own way. What do you need r i g h t  n o w. \n_\nWhat is your body telling you? How can you learn to listen, drop in, take note? \npicture by @withlovebyeva \n_\n#hsp #lifeofanintrovert #embodied #gentlereminder #cyclicalliving #begentle #intuitiveentrepreneur #wildwoman #trustyourpath #trust #surrender #invoelen #yogini #goddessvibes #intuition #lightworker #mindbodyconnection #gentlereminder #soften #become",
