    "post_id": "2081417417032146200",
    "filename": "2019-07-05_2081417417032146090.jpg",
    "description": "When I was little I loved to read my horoscope in the magazines my mum bought, and I guess that love is still here now but it has transferred to monthly forecast podcasts and posts about the new and full moon. \n_\nI love to read forecasts for the new moon and the new month but at some point last year I realise I was listening to 5 podcasts + reading a hundred articles each month, picking up so many ideas from other people, some of them I wanted, some of them that didn‚Äôt really serve me. I stopped listening to my own knowledge and my own inner wisdom, I stopped drawing my own cards, I was giving away my power to someone else and somehow I stopped listening to the knowledge that was already inside me. \n_\nTo get back to myself I had to stop certain things, I stopped listening to monthly forecasts, I unfollowed people that talked about the moon + astrology on here, I started to connect back to what I felt about it, what I knew about it. Learning + unlearning. \n_\nAt this point I‚Äôm back to listening to the musings of a few of my favourite teachers and mentors, @wildsoulhealing ‚Äôs monthly medicine, @sarahmchappell ‚Äôs business forecast, @_ashleywood ‚Äôs  monthly forecast. I do only listen to them after I have done my own rituals, pulled my own tarot cards, tuned into my own intuition. So their views can enhance mine, not cloud them over.\n_\nüì∑ @withlovebyeva \n_\n#beyourownteacher #wildsoul #intuitiveliving #intuition #reconnection #reclaiming #wildwoman #guidance #oracle #tarot #consciousliving #energyworker #embodied #healing #horoscope #monthlymedicine",
