    "filename": "2019-07-10_2084967718963941316.jpg",
    "description": "This week has felt like both a regression and an evolution in many ways. Some sh*t from a couple of years ago came back to the surface and it exposed a lot of unresolved hurt + fears, about my business, about myself, about my relationships to others. \n_\nThis week has felt like a time machine, at times I felt like I was back two years ago, dealing with the same practical issues, feeling the same hurt + overwhelm. Like all the work I did before was somehow useless. But it wasn‚Äôt. This week I got to deal with all the things I couldn‚Äôt all those years ago. I got to take charge of how I handled things, of how I felt about things, I got to take back my agency. Because I now know that things don‚Äôt happen to us. All of this doesn‚Äôt mean that I‚Äôm not incredibly triggered or sad or anxious, because I am. But I also know I am growing and working though layers, and I know that I am supported, by lovely people around me and by myself.\n_\nMercury retrograde is notoriously a time for things coming back to find you + make you deal with them in ways you couldn‚Äôt before, is there something or someone that‚Äôs coming back for you right now? How are you handling it?\n_\nüì∑ @withlovebyeva \n_\n#mercuryretrograde #growth #newlayers #oldwounds #shadowwork #eclipseseason #theplanetsmademedoit #wildsoul #growthisnotlinear #moonchild #soulwork #evolution #nervoussystem #selfcare #innerwork #findinggrace #sisterwound #wildwoman #witchesofinstagram",
