    "filename": "2020-11-23_2448905930084097414.jpg",
    "description": "recovery diaries #1\n\nhere i am, i‚Äôve just turned 29. i‚Äôve been vegan for 5 years, i do yoga, go out for walks . i‚Äôm careful about hormones and bpa and quit the pill a few years ago. i drink nettle tea and kombucha, infuse what i eat and drink with reiki. i‚Äôve worked on my trauma and my life is cyclical and listen to my intuition.\n\ni also have cancer\n\nand the feeling of ‚Äúthis is so unfair‚Äù keeps sneaking in more and more. i did everything right. this was supposed to give me some kind of edge, some kind of controle, some kind of protective bubble. and now i‚Äôm learning to be with that feeling. how we create this sense of safety and controle for ourselves and what we do when it crumbles \n\nthe physical healing is the hardest i‚Äôve ever had to do, but the emotional is as well. the trauma of feeling so betrayed by your body, the trauma of hospitals and treatments, that the thing that is going to heal you will also break down so much of you. it‚Äôs the little things that make me the saddest, losing my cycle and how silly that seems compared to everything. how foreign my body feels with everything rearranged. i‚Äôve lost so much weight i cant regulate my own body temperature and i think about my eating disorder days and how silly it was of me wanting to disappear and take up less space while my body is fighting so hard now to take up more. every day is a struggle and mostly it still feels like me against my body but the moments i can feel her again and realise it‚Äôs actually her that‚Äôs fighting as well, trying so hard as well, are becoming more frequent. i chant to her like a little kid, that i‚Äôm sorry i‚Äôm not patient with her and i know it‚Äôs hard and she‚Äôs trying.\n\nthis is what healing is, the messy in between, it‚Äôs okay to be here. this needs space as well, the hurting, the survival, the grief, the anger. this is what being brave is, it‚Äôs how we keep going every day, it‚Äôs how we try to smile when we‚Äôd rather cry yes, but also it‚Äôs creating space for every aspect of the experience. we need to feel this to make space, we need to go through this to move further.\n_\n#recoverydiaries #cancer #tw #eatingdisorder #healing #becoming #freefall #thefool #embodied",
