    "description": "recovery diaries #3\n\ncancer made me appreciate my body more. it sounds strange but it‚Äôs true. after the initial shock of betrayal and ‚Äúwhy the hell is my body trying to kill me‚Äù there are now waves of pride, of softness. i know she‚Äôs right here with me, trying her best, getting stronger, healing and mending and breaking down all at the same time.\n\nthis is a story of sickness and hurt and carrying things heavier than you ever thought you would have. but most of all it‚Äôs a story about resilience and healing and connection\n\n_\n\ntoday my body can digest food. keep me warm (most of the time). sleep in a bed (I slept upright in a chair for a month after surgery so this is huge). go for walks. pet cats. have sex. take a shower by herself. do yoga and breathe into spaces. handle chemo even if we weren‚Äôt sure that she could already\n\ntoday this body is living and breathing and doing the best she can \n\ntoday this body is pure magic, and maybe that‚Äôs what healing is all about \n_\n#cancerdiaries #recoverydiaries #embodied #livinginabody #thisbodyismagic #healing #becoming",
