    "description": "there‚Äôs still a lot of old programming about ‚Äúdoing‚Äù, about being productive. there‚Äôs still a lot of apologising about needing help, or not being able. there‚Äôs still a lot of shame here, and anger.\n\ndeepening of lessons i‚Äôve been learning throughout the years. how my mind revolts when my body buckles under her own weight. ideas of ‚Äúshould be‚Äù and worth and what it means to be in this worth when you can‚Äôt actually do anything.\n\nand before, the lesson was over as soon as the flu or migraine or panic attack was over, and i learned so many things there but still so much remains. this is like a masterclass, a deep dive, when rest is not just an option but the only option, when being sick is not just for a couple of days but forever.\n\nand so i keep reminding myself that my worth is inherent, it doesn‚Äôt depend on what i do or how much i do or how productive i am. i remind myself that healing is a full time job and i should treat it as such. i remind myself that resting\nis doing, that time is just a construct, that fallow periods are necessary for growth\n\ni remind myself that i am only human and my goal here is to make this body feel as safe as whole as possible, all the rest is just static. \n_\n#youareworthy #productivitymyth #restisradical #healing #healingisafulltimejob #cancerdiaries #moonchild #cronemedicine #darkmoon",
