    "post_id": "2480715927973656600",
    "filename": "2021-01-06_2480715927973656732.jpg",
    "description": "things i didn‚Äôt know about chemo (and you might not either so i‚Äôm sharing them) \n\nthere are different types of chemo and the one i get doesn‚Äôt make me lose hair and as grateful i am about that it‚Äôs also annoying because some people think that means it‚Äôs the ‚Äúeasy‚Äù kind of chemo and trust me, it‚Äôs not \n\ni‚Äôve never been as grateful about anything as getting a port and not having to have my veins pokes every time\n\nit helps to name your chemo. mine is called mister fox (folfox for the people that are in the know) and he is very cute and helping me with the cancer shit\n\nthere is a thing like take away chemo, i kid you not. fox on the go!\n\nnurses will always be fascinated when you ask them if you can hold and reiki your chemo before they start \n\nbowels DO NOT LIKE CHEMO AT ALL. like at all\n\ndrinking iced tea will be easier than drinking water the first few days after chemo\n\nthere are some strange side effects like the way my hand spasms and turns into a lill icicle claw when i touch something cold \n\nyou‚Äôre not supposed to eat sushi on chemo and that might be the saddest thing ever (same with the sex with a condom)\n\nyou haven‚Äôt know fatigue until you‚Äôve had chemo and that is coming from a pro nap queen who has had depleted adrenals for years\n\nchemo brain is a thing and sometimes i forget words or can‚Äôt figure out how to do simple tasks and decide to just stay in the couch because i can‚Äôt figure out what the first step is of getting out of the couch\n\nit‚Äôs hard to love something that is helping you survive but at the same time also killing parts of you you kind of love and need \n\nyou can have cold chills and hot flashes in the same hour and the hot flashes will start as soon as you have put on two extra sweaters, socks and found your heated blanket \n\nyou can‚Äôt really imagine what toxic warfare feels like until you‚Äôve been there (and i sincerely hope you never have to) but the closest thing i can think of is having the worst hangover that‚Äôs never ending in combination with a very bad flu \n\ngood days are the days i am only in pain for an hour and actually manage to go for a walk and maybe read a few pages of a book\n_\n#cancerdiaries #chemo",
