    "post_id": "2519777074261467600",
    "filename": "2021-03-01_2519777074261467497.jpg",
    "description": "i‚Äôve always been so committed to showing the darkness along side the light. to create space for the dark, the show that it can be soft here as well, beautiful in its own way.\n\ni am used to this deep sea/deep soul/deep body diving, and still i recoil from time to time. it‚Äôs only natural, it‚Äôs only normal.\n\ni‚Äôm a scorpio sun, reflector, dark moon baby. i don‚Äôt want the superficial, i want all the shades, all the depth. i want to know about the deepest darkest core.\n\nand yet \n\nand yet\n\nit‚Äôs been a lot of just darkness lately, or at least it feels like it. no silver linings, no end of the tunnel. just pitch black. and then i wonder if i only like the dark when it‚Äôs pretty and palatable and just enough. i wonder how i can be here without being pulled in completely or if maybe getting pulled in completely is the main thing i need right now. i notice how i almost want to curate this experience, make it seem brighter, add a silver lining (or two or three)\n\nbut sometimes it‚Äôs just darkness, and it‚Äôs okay if that makes you uncomfortable because it makes me uncomfortable too\n\nlet‚Äôs be uncomfortable together \n_\n#darknightofthesoul #underworld #discomfort #scorpio #witchythings #onbeing #lunarliving #darkmoon #musings #comfortinthediscomfort #thefool #embodiedtarot #intuition",
