    "post_id": "2530023813065153500",
    "filename": "2021-03-15_2530023813065153622.jpg",
    "description": "things that are happening behind the scenes that i don‚Äôt really know how to show yet:\n\nall the times i spend curled up on a ball in the floor crying my eyes out because i can‚Äôt do a thing, especially when it‚Äôs a simple thing, especially when someone wants to help but i just want to be able to do it myself \n\nall the dissociating that comes with living in a body with pain and how that is not always a bad thing \n\nall the love. when my dad comes over a few days a week to help and always brings chocolate and drinks a million coffees. when my baby sister cooks my a meal when she‚Äôs over. when a sweet friend comes over every weekend to help my poor poor back. when my bf strokes my back during panic attacks because he knows it brings me back.\n\nhow small the world feels when you are stuck in a room and your body barely works and you are facing such complex trauma and people can‚Äôt really understand (thank god they can‚Äôt), how lonely it gets, and scary.\n\nhow i really want to do something for colon cancer month because it‚Äôs basically the ‚Äúleast cool‚Äù cancer and i‚Äôm surrounded by grandpas wherever i look and i want people like me to have a space there too but i don‚Äôt know how or why and i also don‚Äôt have the energy but also it‚Äôs very important \n\nalso: hot flashes, what the hell?!\n_\n#lifelately #cancerdiaries #behindthescenes #coloncancer #darmkanker #brafmutation #living #onbeingalive #soften #feelitall",
    "likes": 270,
