    "description": "‚Äúbut you look so good‚Äù\n\n‚Äúi wasn‚Äôt expecting you to look this good while i was reading your file‚Äù\n\nor my favourite \n\n‚Äúoh but i thought she was doing better, she doesn‚Äôt look sick‚Äù\n\ni can‚Äôt even begin to explain how painful this is, everyone telling me how good i look, that i don‚Äôt look sick. sure it‚Äôs a blessing, but also it‚Äôs constantly battling against perception. it‚Äôs people with angry looks and nasty whispers when you have to lean on your walking cane in the store because you‚Äôre so tired and you‚Äôre holding up the line. it‚Äôs doctors not believing the amount of pain your are in. it‚Äôs distant relatives asking if you are better ‚Äúyet‚Äù when you might not ever get better\n\n_\n\nwhat you see is that i look okay and my eyes sparkle and i sometimes make it outside of the house. what you don‚Äôt see is the 50morphine patch i am wearing, the infection that has been raging in my body for 6 weeks, the bandages i am wearing because puss continues to leak out of my scar, how sometimes i collapse on the floor bc i can‚Äôt possibly walk any further, the panic attacks that come with being a stage 4 cancer patient, how tired my experimental meds are making me\n\ni‚Äôm holding space for both of these version of me, and i hope in time the world can do the same \n_\n#ableisme #lifewithcancer #cancerdiaries #chronicillness #butyoulooksogood #whatbeingsicklookslike #whatcancerlookslike #coloncancer #notawarrior #soften #invisableillness #holdingspace",
