    "post_id": "2592184736581263400",
    "filename": "2021-06-09_2592184736581263271.mp4",
    "description": "when i got sick all the spaces that used to bring me comfort and joy felt wrong. they felt unreal, unsafe, not for me. so i stopped going there, from one day to the other i stopped all my rituals and my tarot draws and my writing. my altars were abandoned, my connection was lost.\n\ni can see now that it was a mix of trauma and how unsafe a space the spiritual world is for us sick people. that i couldn‚Äôt lean on these things because i couldn‚Äôt be in my body, couldn‚Äôt ground my practices down, wasn‚Äôt strong enough to deal with the bullshit.\n\nslowly i am coming back home, leaning back in. tarot came first, like an old friend, drawing a card and then leaving my deck for a month, or holding it close and shuffling without picking a card. the comfort of old rituals and the presence of the tarot was enough. i started writing again, praying. i started to miss my altar and learning more about every day magic, messy magic, small magic.\n\ni found my way back and in that journey there was a lot of shifting and shedding. old beliefs or practices they i had outgrown, new ways of seeing the world, a new found focus on grounding, embodiment. \n\ni‚Äôm so curious to see how my intuition and practices will further evolve, with this new solid, safe foundation i am building \n\nhoney i‚Äôm home\nit feels so good to be back \n_\n#spirituality #eclipseseason #trauma #growth #embodiment #grounding #witchythings #moonchild #oracle #tarot #intuitivetarot #safespace #altar #thereisaplaceforyou #foundations #becoming #soften #tattoos #rituals #cleansing #shedding",
