    "description": "and every time i think i have already learned so much about presence and embodiment there is always another layers, a new nuance to lean into \n\nthis week is about presence in the softest and realest ways. it‚Äôs about learning that you can have a bad morning and a good day. that it‚Äôs okay to rest during and in between activities. \n\nthat rest isn‚Äôt waiting but being\n\nit‚Äôs all the seasons in one day and not getting attached to them, knowing that even when you are dead tired now, you can still catch a second (or third or fourth) wind.\n\nthis is cyclical living as well, for years i focused on the bigger cycles, the moon, my own cycle. i lost connection to it for a while, losing my compass in all that and now it comes back in some ways, but like everything it‚Äôs more in the everyday, the magical in the mundane\n\nfor years i practised being in the void, i learned that there is always new light after dark moon phases, now i‚Äôm embodying that in a whole new way, moment to moment.\n_\n#cyclicalliving #embodiment #spoonylife #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #darkmoon #livinginabody #chronicillness #soften #restissacred #mindful #onbeinghere #flowerchild #moonchild",
