    "description": "there are good weeks, weeks i can almost believe that my body is able and my mind is free and i m just another human, living my life. and then there are weeks like this one, i forget how horrible they are every time after a day or two but in the thick of it i imagine this is what purgatory most be like (this and hospital waiting rooms)\n\nevery day there‚Äôs the hope and then the reality. the not being able to do even the simple things, when taking a shower and having lunch and drinking enough are the biggest struggles. when scrolling and watching mindless tv is all i can do. it‚Äôs like i can feel my body and my mind dissolve\n\nalong with the immobility comes the pain, my hips and back are burning but i can‚Äôt shake it out. i‚Äôve been ‚Äútraining‚Äù for daily walks and i know i will have to start the process over again. i have to keep eating because i have to take my meds, you know the ones that are keeping me alive, but eating is also the hardest thing ever\n\nit might seem like a nice time out when your life is busy, but trust me, resting, especially having to rest, gets very old after a day or two, stuck in your body, when you can‚Äôt even read or do something engaging and all there is left is waiting\n\ni know this will pass as well. that it‚Äôs the ebb and flow, better days will come as they always do, but right now it doesn‚Äôt feel like that, so i rest, i wait, i specialise in pit pull videos and let the cats sleep on top of me for hours\n\ninhale \nexhale\ni am here\nthis is life too\n_\n#lifewithcancer #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #spoonielife #chronicallyill #unrest #soften #napfluencer #feelingitall #embodied #cats #therapoes #brafmutation",
