    "description": "void\n\nall i feel some days is sad, empty. it‚Äôs been almost a year, coming up on my ‚Äúanniversary‚Äù. you‚Äôd think a year would be enough to get used to a situation but i don‚Äôt think any amount of time would be enough to get used to this\n\na year ago they told me that by now i‚Äôd be on the mend, recuperating, healing. and then a few month later that i might not ever get better. so what happens when you stay sick (at least you are lucky for not getting sicker)? what happens when days become months, become years? and there is always this faint hope that next time things will get and stay better, but also always this fear that maybe this is the best you‚Äôll ever be and it will only go downhill from here?\n\nit‚Äôs living the line between fear and hope, between good enough and not nearly okay. it‚Äôs being grateful and sad and angry and all the other things in between\n\ni am void\nempty\ngutted\n\ntrying to live a life that feels so small, that feels like it will suffocate me. trying to be happy with the little things but wanting the big things so badly. trying to built something that will add up to more than just waiting, just surviving \n\n(written on a bad day, on good days i‚Äôll probably tell you a different story)\n_\n#whatcancerlookslike #bowelcancer #braf #embodiment #baddays #feelitall #surviving #nervoussystemcare #becoming #void #darkmoon #moonchild #soften #photography #creatrix",
