    "description": "body\n\nthis week i bought pregnancy pants and a stoma support band, after weeks of feeling defensive about it. finally excepting that they are going to help me find back some freedom on my body and the way i dress, they they will allow me to wear more of the outfits i loved but haven‚Äôt been wearing because i don‚Äôt feel confident or comfortable on them\n\nthis week i had s*x for the first time again after months of being in too much pain, or too tired, or dealing with menopausal issues, or not feeling comfortable with having two stoma bags\n\nthis week i made lentil soup and ate crisp apples and nuts from the tree in my garden, so simple yet so magical. exactly the types of things i used to eat all the time before\n\nif you look at me, i‚Äôm starting to look a lot like the Maxime of before, i have a fuller face again, i can wear the same clothes again, eat the same things, it might seem like i always was this but this past year has been an underworld journey that took me deeper than i‚Äôve ever had to go. my body still carries the scars and the memories(and also my body still has cancer, we shouldn‚Äôt forget that)\n\nfor most of the time this past year my body hasn‚Äôt been mine, she has been a project, a riddle, to be prodded in, meddled with, filled with products and medicine. but in this moment, sitting in the sun, with a cup of warm tea in my hand, she is completely mine. and i am reclaiming her with every little act of self love \n\nmore and more she is starting to feel like myself, like my own again\n_\n#embodied #livinginabody #selflove #bodyneutrality #selfcare #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #stomalife #feminine #oracle #moonchild #softness #healing #underworld #trauma #medicaltrauma #darkmoon #thebodykeepsthescore",
