    "filename": "2021-10-20_2688687638682121629.jpg",
    "description": "incurable \n\nwe had only just settled into the waiting room, months of these appointments and we learned that the oncology waiting room is kind of a limbo and a marathon all in one. so i was joking with the oncologist about how this was the shortest wait ever as we walked in because i get super chatty when i‚Äôm nervous and he asked me how i‚Äôm doing and i politely answer while all we really want to do is skip this part and hear about the scans.\n\neverything is stable, you are doing so great\n\nand it‚Äôs the first time that i want to ask the question, that i really want to know. previous appointments i dogged it and didn‚Äôt want to hear the specifics, reading between the lines was heartbreaking enough.\n\n‚Äúso is this still curative treatment or how would we describe this dance we are doing?‚Äù\n\nhe takes a breath and looks into my eyes and tries to formulate a few different answers at the same time. we already knew it, in a way, we already felt it but it‚Äôs the first time that someone actually says it out loud\n\nincurable \n\nthe treatment i‚Äôm on right now won‚Äôt cure me and they can‚Äôt operate and we don‚Äôt really have other options. but as long as i stay stable and the meds keep working and i can handle the side effects this is what it is. chronic cancer, or whatever we want to call this option. we don‚Äôt really talk or hear about this side of cancer a lot but the group of people like me is getting bigger every day. the group that isn‚Äôt dying but also will never be cured. we are living in a limbo of our own\n_\n#thisiswharcancerlookslike #braf #coloncancer #incurablecancer #immunotherapy #soften #embodied #healthupdate #chronicillness #underworldjourney #thevoid #limbo",
