    "post_id": "2725712056081179000",
    "filename": "2021-12-10_2725712056081179191.jpg",
    "description": "how messy it is living in the void\n\nour hands tainted with tears and blood and faith. lighting candles,\nnot really knowing whether we are doing it to invite in some warmth or because the ritual of it gives us comfort\n\nthe good day are as humbling as the bad ones. we visit this church and i light a candle and have goosebumps all over my arms because this feels sacred. as sacred as the nights spent in the comfort of you and a glass of wine and the lights down low, as sacred as the days spent in a haze of fever and scans and an iv line drip drip dripping \n\nnothing really happens but at the same time everything does. my body is slowly leaning back into parasympathetic mode and i‚Äôm in awe with her willingness, how much she wants to heal and build and function. i dream the most vivid dreams. pleas and prayers to find something meaningful to do. creations and ideas seeping into my mind when i‚Äôm resting. the weight of the cats napping next to me, one next to my belly, one in the half moon shape behind my knees\n\ni always thought the void was a static thing but it turns out, like everything else, it had cycles of its own, new beginnings and layers and  nuance. and so i‚Äôm entering a new phase and it‚Äôs still dark but in a different way and it still hurts but not like it did before\n\nthe magical and the mundane and the embodied and the weightless living so close next to each other. all these things that i am learning and feeling and i don‚Äôt know how to talk about them yet except in riddles\n_\n#musingsfromthevoid #embodied #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #nervoussystemcare #everydaymagic #ritual #darkmoon #oracle #moonchild #cyclicalliving #livingthecrone #whatitmeanstobealive #becoming #soften #chronicalillness #embodiedtarot",
