    "description": "i‚Äôm sitting on a soft pillow, cup of tea in hand, looking at the flicker of a candle and all these treasures i‚Äôve gathered all around me. there‚Äôs a cat sleeping on the cosy chair next to me, journal at my feet, rain pattering on the roof\n\nit‚Äôs such a mundane moment, a sweet moment waking up in front of my altar the way i have done a million times before. and it‚Äôs also so meaningful because it‚Äôs the first time since i got sick that i managed to do it. i‚Äôve missed these mornings at my altar, mornings filled with silence and writing and tarot and crystals and restlessness and connection and feelings\n\nmornings used to be my safe heaven as much as my altar space was. and then for a while mornings became the hardest part of the day. and i missed them, the time for myself to tune in and connect and start my day in a grounded way. this morning felt so familiar but also so magical, it felt like recovering a part of myself,coming home.\n\nlittle by little i‚Äôm coming back to myself \n\n_\npic 1-3 current altar spaces, pic 4-5 first altar space i ever created \n_\n#morningritual #cyclicalliving #gratitude #soften #altar #safespace #ritual #healing #meditation #toth #embodiment #oracle #intuition #selfcare #treasures #magpie #abundance #mermaid #moonchild",
