    "post_id": "2749657036315127000",
    "filename": "2022-01-12_2749657036315127023.jpg",
    "description": "a year can make a huge difference\n\nlast year i was so sick, recuperating from a massive surgery, on a chemo that was breaking me apart and cancer slowly creeping back into my body. i was so skinny and so cold and in so much pain. we celebrated christmas a week early bc i had a chemo infusion scheduled a few days before christmas day. the whole winter of last year was rock bottom, living with a broken spirit in a broken body and not being sure if i would even make it a few more months. and then this year i am here, i still have cancer but for now i‚Äôm stable and i can actually do things, i‚Äôm not in pain 24/7, i can eat food and celebrate and go for walks and can create. it‚Äôs a miracle i‚Äôm here, and the way i‚Äôm here is even more miraculous.\n\nso this is a gentle reminder, that a year can make all the difference in the world. that there is always a world beyond rock bottom, even when you can‚Äôt feel into that while you are in it. this is a gentle reminder that things can be unbearably hard and also incredibly beautiful, that these two realities can (and most of the time) will live right next to each other\n_\nthe photographs are a series of right now compared to the same things last year \n_\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #coloncancer #darmkanker #braf #lifewithcancer #embodied #soften #duality #alive #healing #becoming #chronicillness #oracle #winter #cyclicalliving #lifedeathrebirth",
