    "description": "it‚Äôs very fragile, the way my body feels. it can be shifted in a minute by just about anything and there is not a lot i can do about that. being sick, getting treatment, most of it is about allowing people to do, things happening to you and with you. there isn‚Äôt agency here. no controle. \n\na couple of days ago i had an infusion and today i feel frayed around the edges, reminded of the fragility of my health. there‚Äôs no a lot i can do about it but there are others things i can do\n\ni get to site outside in the sunshine and write and drink tea. i get to move my body and drop into how good that can feel. i get to take deep nap ms with weights on my hands and eyes, binaural beets in my ears. i focus on hydration. these are the things i get to do to make myself feel better. i get to take care of myself and live in a body that can still feel unmitigated joy, with my face in the sun, a steaming mug of tea in my hands\n\nthis what selfcare had turned in for me, supporting my body through it all, holding myself in the process of allowing and letting go\n_\n#selfcare #nervoussystemcare #healing #soften #deeprest #napfluencer #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #supportsystem #embodied #embodiedselfcare #yoga #reiki #bowelcancer #moonchild #cyclicalliving #intuition #nourishment #womenwhorunwiththewolves #wildwoman #crone",
