    "post_id": "2758350876279473000",
    "filename": "2022-01-24_2758350876279473071.mp4",
    "description": "reclaiming. becoming. rebirthing\n\ni remind myself that this is a life worth living. it is my mantra, a continuous echo in the hollow of my spine, on the days when i feel like i‚Äôm crawling and scratching and barely hanging on, on the days when the light and the softness of my sweater and your voice is so unbearably beautiful. \n\nthis is a life. it‚Äôs worth living. it beats in my chest and it surges through my veins. \n\nit is\nit has to be\ni am creating it\n\ni write about all the parts of myself i am missing and how i might invite them back. i miss having a body that has more space, that has room for creation and processes and magic. that isn‚Äôt consumed by pain or fatigue or worry. i invite in pieces of my core self through music and the lens of my camera and the rhythm of my words. i wear lipstick and skirts and bask in the sun and call it worship. sometimes i dream i am already dead and i am transformed and another version of me again.\n\nbringing back and letting go. shedding layer after layer after layer and discovering that what is left is always the same and always completely different. i am me. at the core i always am and will be and no experience can take that away.\n\nthis is a life worth living and i want to life it through all of its incarnations\n_\njournal musings from this afternoon, sitting in the sun on my favourite bench, photo 4-5 are early 2020 versions of me\n_\n#musings #journal #mantra #soften #becoming #incarnation #creatrix #moonchild #cyclicalliving #grievingpastselves #soul #livinginthevoid #thecrone #blooming #embodiedtarot #rebirth #phoenix #reclamation #lifewithcancer",
