    "post_id": "2773639269551296500",
    "filename": "2022-02-14_2773639269551296372.jpg",
    "description": "i am birthing\non the cusp of a transformation, contractions in the form of writing and insights and eating good food and just generally taking care of myself \n\nthere is a new chapter in my life as an incurable ill embodied person just around the corner, a new version of being in this part of my life that i could have never imagined to be so alive and in flux. there have been many versions of me in this journey and this newest version is making the jump from surviving to living.\n\nthere‚Äôs a softening here and also a newfound solidity, safety, trust. i am stepping into a sort of agency, the notion that i will be here for however long it will be but i do have the choice to do more than just be lived by it.\n\ni‚Äôve been discovering the flow and the rhythm and the layers here, that incurable is not just one thing but a kaleidoscope of all the things. the urge to actually create a life here.\n\nliving is about more than just not dying \n\n_\n#musings #embodied #moonchild #cyclicalliving #selfportrait #whatcancerlookslike #incurableillness #transformation #soften #becoming #oracle #creatrix #alifeworthliving #bowelcancer #brafmutation",
