    "post_id": "2782215962105258500",
    "filename": "2022-02-26_2782215962105258409.jpg",
    "description": "ìè≤ gentle reminder ìè≤\n\ndon‚Äôt let anyone ever tell you you are not doing it the right way\n\nyour life, your job, your spirituality, your relationships, your illness\n\nyou are the one living and moving through it, doing the best you can, going with the flow of things. you are the only one that can decide what is right for you.\n\nìè≤\n\ni share my musings here as an oracle and a former body worker and a partner and someone who loves to create and an incurably ill person. i should know better by now but every single time i‚Äôm astounded by the amount of messages i get with advice, there‚Äôs no end to the ‚Äúdo you know what your illness is trying to teach you‚Äù and ‚Äúi‚Äôve cured myself by doing this‚Äù and ‚Äúyou should consider this‚Äù. \n\ni‚Äôm sharing my life here, the way i‚Äôm living it, the way i‚Äôm dealing with it, all the things that come up from me and how i choose to engage with them (i mean not all of them, it‚Äôs still social media and some things are just meant to be private). there is not a problem with it, my life is not something that has to be fixed. i‚Äôm not something that has to be fixed\n_\n#gentlereminder #iamwhole #chronicillness #incurableillness #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #becoming #soften #unsollicitedadvice #livingwithincurablecancer",
    "likes": 118,
