    "filename": "2022-03-17_2796075194084935349.jpg",
    "description": "ìè≤ gentle reminder ìè≤\n\nwe are not meant to always be healing and growing\n\nthere is a lot of emphasis on self help these days, we are busy healing past trauma and supporting our nervous systems and being embodied and becoming better versions of ourselves. \n\nit‚Äôs part of life (if you want it to be) but it‚Äôs not the point of life. the point of life is to live. \n\nand yes sometimes that means dealing with demons and learning lessons, but we are not put on this planet to be looking at inner work like it‚Äôs our daytime job. we are not here just to evolve and learn and become the best versions of ourselves. that‚Äôs a capitalist vision of spirituality and healing, that‚Äôs us being hell bent on having there be an end result and a goal and the end of the road. that‚Äôs how we want to look at live to have it make sense, but it‚Äôs not life.\n\nìäì\n\nthis is what i‚Äôve been learning through the years, what my guides keep whispering to me, it‚Äôs very simple\n\nìè≤ you are already enough, you are already exactly we‚Äôre you are supposed to be. you are worthy the way you are. we want you to live, to experience and create. to do all these things that you can only do here, fold into yourself, soften into your body, breathe in beauty and manifest creations. \n\nyou don‚Äôt have to work so hard, try so hard, there is no need to keep picking everything apart. it‚Äôs very simple, you‚Äôre here to live, to experience. good things, bad things,  boring things, exciting things, neutral things. that the point of life, living ìè≤\n\n_\n#channeledmessage #oracle #youareenough #gentlereminder #selfcare #nervoussystem #healing #soften #becoming #embodied #beinghuman #selfportrait",
