    "filename": "2022-03-22_2799795355141761263.mp4",
    "description": "today i cried so hard my eyes are puffy still. i went outside and felt the warm sun on my bare back. i dissociated what feels like a million times.i spoke gentle words to myself because i know dissociation is just my nervous system trying to keep me safe. i told myself that i am safe. i thought about what actions i could take to make me feel safe and opted for mindless movies and soft blankets and cbd oil and feet in the grass and crying and xanax. i fought with my husband over video call. i sent sweet messages and memes and ginger tea and care packages for the isolation den to him. i reached out to people even if/especially because i wanted to shut everyone out. i tried to drink enough. i didn‚Äôt eat enough but i‚Äôm okay with that because i tried my best. i sat in front of my altar and marvelled at the smoke and walked around the whole house because i read somewhere that smoke can kill bacteria.\n\ni‚Äôm not as resilient. to be honest i never was that resilient to begin with but being ill and fatigued and all the trauma and all the stress, it left only a very tiny cloud of resilience available for me. the bad days can be pretty bad but i‚Äôm getting better at them. i‚Äôm finding grace in them, accepting that this is what my nervous system does, honouring that she‚Äôs trying to help and trying to help her in return.\n\ntoday was a really hard day. i did as best as i could and i‚Äôm really proud of myself.\n\n_\n#mentalhealth #trauma #medicaltrauma #healing #soften #itsokay #nervoussystemcare #selfcare #journaling #selfportrait #smokecleansing #ritual #iamsafe #dissociation #grace #baddays #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #feelitall #embodied #resilience #cat #catphotography",
