    "post_id": "2809018779533703000",
    "filename": "2022-04-04_2809018779533703114.mp4",
    "description": "to be honest i didn‚Äôt expect to see another spring. last year, when the world was coming alive in bursts of colour and fluff and sunshine, i was told that i was slowly dying. i had a bad feeling about the chemo i was on, the pain i was still having even though i was technically cancer free. i though it was only normal, with the trauma and the fact that chemo is supposed to be gruelling. but then the scans proved that i was right and treatment was failing and the cancer was back and there was one final option we could try that might stabilise me. \n\nwe‚Äôd had a cascade of bad news turning into worse news turning into the worst news since october, this was the latest proof that there was a level under what i thought was rock bottom. it was also the first time i started to feel hopeful. the first step into stepping back into my body and her intuition. \n\ni started the new meds and spent all the time i felt good enough staring at the gorgeous blossoming trees, smelling the flowers and the soil at dusk. on the days i felt like crap i sat in my bouncy chair in front of the big windows to watch the blooming trees across the road. i stabilised. i look at photographs from that time and see the light slowly return back to my eyes.\n\ni‚Äôm so grateful to be here for another year of spring. the promise that there is always a chance of renewal, rebirth. being part of this magic with my feet in the grass, looking up at the tall trees and seeing how they are transformed every day. \n_\nphoto 2,3 and 4 are from last spring, the rest are this years spring wonders \n_\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #bowelcancer #braf #stage4needsmore #incurablyill #thediffenceayearmakes #odetospring #spring #rebirth #photography #selfportrait #inbloom #soften #becoming #moonchild #lovelettertospring",
    "likes": 164,
