    "post_id": "2812601878334384000",
    "filename": "2022-04-09_2812601878334384208.jpg",
    "description": "small town life is healing me in ways i didn‚Äôt even realise i needed healing. this house has been the biggest blessing during this whole whirlwind season. it‚Äôs a place to call home, to come back to, to feel safe. i had been dreaming of a house with a garden, longing for a safe haven, something to nest and create in but it always felt as something for later. when i was done with living in the city and ready to settle down. when i had saved enough money. and then life changed so rapidly and a lot of things fell away, became so insignificant. only this one thing kept coming back, feeling not only true but vital.\n\nthe longing for a home, a safe space. a garden to sit in and grow herbs. a space that could hold me and all my hurt and dreams. that could hold us and the family we wanted to be.\n\nit‚Äôs the rhythm i‚Äôve always longed for, a slow safe life. it‚Äôs a paradox because nothing about my life feels particularly slow or safe most of the time, on paper it‚Äôs not, yet in reality in most ways it is. \n\nit‚Äôs an initiation. homing. the ability to feel safe in the deepest uncertainty, the biggest tower moments. it‚Äôs trusting in our ability to grow roots in the midst of fire. it‚Äôs the realisation that even in this, life goes in. even here there is joy.\n_\n#lifewithcancer #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #homing #embodied #tarot #embodiedtarot #orcale #intuitiveliving #cyclicalliving #safe #nervoussystem #medicaltrauma #home #soften #becoming #spring #homeiswheretheheartis #rest #sacredrest #sacredspace #bloomon #flowers #napfluencer #selfportrait #catlover #stage4colorectalcancer #bowelcancer #braf",
