    "post_id": "2830082404573253600",
    "filename": "2022-05-03_2830082404573253622.jpg",
    "description": "selfcare is not some magical, ephemeral formula that you can learn from someone else.\nselfcare is a set of skills. it‚Äôs learning what works for you and what doesn‚Äôt. it‚Äôs taking care of your body and your nervous system and your soul and your heart all at once. it‚Äôs a muscle, you have to work it, train it, spent time with it.\n\nselfcare for me is waking up in pain and utterly fatigued and using all the energy and willpower i have to take my meds, make myself a cup of tea and a warm water bottle. because i know i will feel worse when i am dehydrated, because i know that warmth will do me good and meds are necessary. it‚Äôs anything but fancy, or aesthetic. it‚Äôs coaxing myself outside in the sunshine because i know it fills up my heart and helps my body heal. it‚Äôs doing a bit of movement everyday and learning to listen to my body to know what is enough because the rules keep changing.\n\nabove all, selfcare for me had been a radical act of leaning in and trustful in my own knowledge. listening to my own body and intuition. learning to take care of myself in all the various, kaleidoscopic ways in which i now exist in this world. it‚Äôs unlearning what health and movement and spirituality look like. and it‚Äôs learning not to look at what anyone else is doing.\n\nselfcare is the art of living in this disabled, uncurably ill body and taking care of her as best as possible, listening to her as closely as i can.\n\nselfcare is a spell. a riot. a ritual. a blessing. an act of radical love and defiance.\n_\n#selfcare #embodiment #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #bowelcancer #embodiedtarot #hierophant #soften #become #intuitiveliving #cyclicalliving #selfcareasaspell #selfcareasaritual #incurablyill #chronicillness #oracle",
