    "filename": "2022-05-11_2835954873746276251.jpg",
    "description": "i did a story archive time travel a couple of mornings ago while i was lying on the couch with a hot water bottle waiting for pain meds to kick in at 5 in the morning. it seemed like a logical activity and a side note is that your story archive here on insta is the most fun diary and i highly recommend building one for yourself, you will not regret it\n\nback to the time travel, it‚Äôs so important for me to look into those flashbacks because i tend to forget how far i‚Äôve actually come. it‚Äôs interesting to see me using the same phrases i use right now, i talk about immuno therapy being okay, especially after being on chemo for months, how grateful i am for being able to do more things and also how annoyed i get when there‚Äôs a set back. the phrases are the same, the reality isn‚Äôt. last year versus now is day and night. i‚Äôve been getting so much stronger and can do so much more and it is crucial for me to take time to recognise that, to celebrate it.\n\nthis becomes even more important on the hard days, to see how far i‚Äôve come, to know that i can still bounce back and grow. to trust that this is the ebb and flow of my life now and that i am resilient. to continue learning that a few bad days do not make a bad life. so today i look back and i‚Äôm in awe of the person i was a year ago and the person i am now, i take the time to celebrate how far i‚Äôve come. a year ago it seemed like a dream to ever be able to do the things i can do now\n_\npic 2: archive from may 2021 || pic 3-7: may 2021 || pic 8-10: this week\n_\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #thereislifehere #growth #healing #embodiment #reflection #innerwork #soften #selfcare #nervoussystemhealth #celebrate #silverlinings #cyclicalliving #slowlife #moonchild",
