    "post_id": "2848949254238621000",
    "filename": "2022-05-29_2848949254238621351.mp4",
    "description": "i used to love going to music concerts on my own, really allowing myself to soak in the experience, flow to the music. it‚Äôs been about 2 years since i last went to a concert and at some point last year i was sure i would never be able to do it again. it‚Äôs still something i won‚Äôt be able to do on my own or in the way i used to.but we adept and we overcome and this past week i went to two concert, a rooftop concert at museum m and the warpaint concert at ab\n\nit felt so so awesome to be listening and dancing to live music again, i felt so grateful to be there, especially since it has been a very emotionally challenging week and music does make things better.  it also came with its fair share of sadness and grief. i would have loved to be dancing with my husbands at a spot close to the stage but that‚Äôs not an option anymore and i am so grateful both events and venues were so disability friendly and i got to attend in a way that was comfortable for me\n\nit can be really hard and confronting to not be able to do things the way you used to be able to do them and i sometimes have the urge to just not do those things anymore to spare myself all the heartache. in this case i am really glad i searched for a compromise, it brought me so much joy and inspiration\n_\n#embodied #concerts #warpaint #inuit #adventure #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #chronicillness #accesability #disabledbodies #stage4needsmore #incurableillness #soften #lifecanbegood #makingmemories #memorybox",
