    "post_id": "2865564716790905000",
    "filename": "2022-06-21_2865564716790904618.jpg",
    "description": "when it‚Äôs the summer solstice but also grey outside and you have just gone on a major trip and your body is still recuperating and all you wanna do is lay on the couch under your gravity blanket all day intermittently napping, eating cookies and watching reality tv but you have also been brainwashed by years in the capitalist and spiritual living world to think that that is a waste of time and a special portal should always be honoured\n\n‚âò\n\nunlearning is learning that our inner seasons don‚Äôt always match the outer seasons and there is no such thing as a wasted day. unlearning is knowing that rest is the most radical thing and if you don‚Äôt feel like big inner work and creation and output it is totally okay to do nothing and take it easy\n\non these kind of days there can be a lot of info going around on what we ‚Äúshould/have to do‚Äù or what would be the ‚Äúright way‚Äù to take advantage of the energy and i am saying f*ck that. you are the only one living in your body and feeling your emotions today and it‚Äôs much more valuable to go with your intuition and do what feels best for you than to do worry about what you should be doing\n\nalso a gentle reminder is that your internal energy and compass will always be more important than the external energy and it‚Äôs okay to tune out the noise about what is happening externally if that is what you need to be more in tune with yourself \n\n‚âò\nhad to think of this @theapricotmemoirs piece while i was writing this so im including it on the third slide\n_\n#cyclicalliving #embodied #solstice #energywork #livinginabody #soften #healing #restissacred #unlearning #innerwork #void #becoming #poetry #summervibes #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #oracle #sacredspace #theapricotmemoirs #nourishment #napfluencer #reflector #humandesign",
