    "post_id": "2883746125699119600",
    "filename": "2022-07-16_2883746125699119851.jpg",
    "description": "i don‚Äôt have the words for this season yet and if there are words they don‚Äôt really make sense. my journal right now is a jumble of half formed thoughts, whispers, ranting, prayers\n\ni still write though, even when it feels like there is nothing to write\n\nit‚Äôs the only way i know to make sense of things, the first way i learned to communicate with myself and with spirit. those connections feel especially lost right now, hidden in the dark, it‚Äôs like the line is dead, but i keep writing. words and phrases. some days i rant and rave, pages full of fears and hurts and memories. despair. some days it‚Äôs a phrase that‚Äôs stuck in my head and i have to write it down just the silence it, to stop it from echoing in the back of my mind\n\ni‚Äôve written more tarot musings (that‚Äôs what i call my tarot readings/channelings in my journal) the past week than i have in the past year. when i‚Äôm doing the actual writing it feels like such a mess, it feel like a mixture of clawing and holding my breath. when i take a step back and look at it all together, it looks like healing\n\nit both surprises and delights me that i‚Äôve chosen to turn to journaling and tarot in this moment because for a long time in similar moments those were the last things i wanted to reach out to. it teaches me that i‚Äôm ready for connection again, i‚Äôm ready for the messy work, for picking apart the layers and letting myself bleed and really living through the lessons. i‚Äôm ready to let something bigger guide me\n\nit‚Äôs perspective. the knowing that right now is hard and it feels like there is no way to go, no way that this will ever be softer. the knowing that it will get better and this is a part of the process and the hard part is almost over. this come with years and years of experience in falling apart. not that this makes it any less hard or scary, but i do know, really, deeply, heartfelt  know in my core and in my bones, that i am okay. that i am working through it in the best way i know \n\nthis is how it‚Äôs supposed to feel, this is what it‚Äôs supposed to look like. this is the way we grow and learn and heal\n_\n#embodiedtarot #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #healing #embodied #soften #themoon #void #iamsafe",
