    "description": "i don‚Äôt have a lot of words right now\n\nmy well has dried up, or maybe it‚Äôs just my access to it, or that my body and mind are so busy doing different things and they kind have lost their way\n\nit‚Äôs a strange sensation, feeling so cut off. lose. words are how i make sense of the world and without them things hardly make sense or maybe things don‚Äôt make sense and that‚Äôs why there are no words\n\ni‚Äôm still writing, sitting with my journal, jotting down phrases and feelings and telling myself that this is writing too, the mud and the mess and the thinking, going in circles, day after day of no words or too many of them and still not really saying anything. im going through the motions but the connection isn‚Äôt there \n\nit‚Äôs a season. it‚Äôs a phase. it will pass. \n\ni tell myself that all the stories are happening in my body right now and as soon as they are processed the words will find me again. i inhale. i exhale. i drink all the water and order herbs online because that‚Äôs what the whispers tell me. i wait for scans next week and to feel a bit better and softer. i wait for the safety and the balance and the feeling of me and the words to find me again\n\ni‚Äôll be right here, resting, breathing, yearning, pen to paper and tarot cards in my hands and hands open with my palms to the sky. open. waiting until im ready to dive a bit deeper again, until it feels safe to connect again. \n\nthere is something sacred here too, of course there is, it‚Äôs always like that \n_\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #depression #embodied #soften #becoming #selfportrait #waiting #scanxiety #tarot #cyclicalliving #darknightofthesoul #thevoid #intuitivetarot #mud #writersblock #creatrix",
