    "post_id": "2895360274841132500",
    "filename": "2022-08-01_2895360274841132496.jpg",
    "description": "i‚Äôm coming up on 22 months of having cancer, about a year of that being aware that they wouldn‚Äôt be able to cure me. next week there are scans and the week after we review and hopefully can continue treatment as we are. it always brings up a lot of feelings, these 3 month marks. \n\nwe‚Äôre in the long haul now, living with cancer. in the beginning of a trauma/chaos/life change/rock bottom it‚Äôs all urgency and flight or fight. all deep talks and feeling life so vividly. technicolour. all panic attacks and cries and pages and pages writing about life and death and purpose.\n\nthat‚Äôs not a way to live in the long term, our minds and bodies and souls can‚Äôt continue in that kind of turmoil for ever, so we do this amazing things and kind of get used to it. the being sick, the mortality issue, the mental and physical aspects. i say kind of because you don‚Äôt really get used to is as much as you really, weirdly do. \n\nscan time are like a reset of the clock, it makes us aware again of what is the reality of my situation. that i am very sick, that i won‚Äôt ever be not sick, that the treatment i am on is keeping me stable but we don‚Äôt know if it will stay that way. enter identity crisis. enter all the feels.\n\nso that‚Äôs where i am right now, in the void. right now the void is the last sunny patch of our garden under our rose bush. it‚Äôs not a bad void to lounge in for sure. this, you also get used to, it seems\n_\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #scanxiety #stagefourneedsmore #bowelcancer #brafmutation #cyclicalliving #soften #smelltheroses #incurableillness #selfportrait #photgraphy #becoming #void",
    "likes": 127,
