    "description": "a short story called ‚Äúwhen you learn your cancer might be active again‚Äù\n\ni get up from my seat and walk toward the door that the doctor is holding open, try to give him a brave smile but since it doesn‚Äôt reach my eyes and im wearing a mask, he won‚Äôt see it. not for the first time i think about how weird it is that we have actually never seen each other‚Äôs faces, this person that i share the deepest, most intimate relationship with. who knows my insides better than i know them myself, prods into my belly and my bloods, gets to tell me every 3 months whether i get to live or die\n\ni grab hold of your hand, trying my best to walk as fast as possible through the waiting room and the hallways, to the stairs and the lobby, plowing our way from the farthest part of the hospital towards the exit so we can finally talk off our masks and take a deep breath. i tell you how i already had a bad feeling about this one and you squeeze my hand once which is code for ‚Äúi know‚Äù and ‚Äúi can‚Äôt really talk right now or i might cry‚Äù and ‚Äúi love you‚Äù and ‚Äúi am so sorry/i am so scared‚Äù\n\ni make us buy ice cream in that little shop we walk past when we have almost made it to the exit, the one i buy all my snacks before infusions. i notice that the cashier can see the tears in my eyes and try to blink them away while we pay and she tells us to enjoy our day and i can feel your grip tighten on my hand. as soon as we are out those double doors we both start talking at the same time. you say you wanted to punch the cassiere when she said to have a nice day, i tell you i don‚Äôt know how i have to tell this to my dad. (continued in comments)\n_\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #embodied #bowelcancer #brafmutation #stage4needsmore #livinginthevoid #writer #musings #oracle #moonchild #soften #love",
