    "post_id": "2914035604733856000",
    "filename": "2022-08-27_2914035604733855607.mp4",
    "description": "‚âò here‚Äôs your gentle reminder that processing big things often looks very boring ‚âò\n\nit doesn‚Äôt matter if your big thing is something physical or mental or emotional or energetic, whether it‚Äôs something ‚Äúgood‚Äù or ‚Äúbad‚Äù. these things take time to settle, our bodies and minds and systems need time to calibrate and incorporate what happened\n\nthis is the parts they don‚Äôt show in movies, or they do it in a quirky montage with upbeat music to signify the passage of time. this is the part they gloss over in stories because we all want to hear the about the actual miracle but not the hard work in the mud and the silence that comes before it, the months of mundane eat/sleep/repeat. processing is very much the part we would rather skip over, especially in our quick win/instant gratification culture, this is the part where it seems/feels like nothing is happening while actually it ALL is happening in this space, in the openness, the vastness, the void. planting the seed is actually the easy part, all the energy and work and hope comes in the part after, where something is working to create a flower and let her bloom.\n\nso here‚Äôs an example of what my processing looks at the moment. there has been some very big energetic shifts with some huge insights happening for me this week and i am so excited for everything to come together and to share the stories that will emerge from here but i also think it is very important to share what this in between space is looking like for me right now because this is where all the magic is actually happening and it‚Äôs the part we often don‚Äôt really see.\nprocessing right now looks like sleeping a lot, 12hr nights and naps in the morning and the afternoon. it looks like spending my days in pjs, reading books, a mix of memoirs and poetry and novels i am reading for the 5th time. watching reality tv, selling the oc just came out and it feels like perfect timing. all of these things are helping me create space, an opening to feel and heal and process.",
