    "post_id": "2919766982363243000",
    "filename": "2022-09-04_2919766982363243245.jpg",
    "description": "i watch the sky shift from blue to pink to dark, birds flying by, the sounds of the outside world seeping in through the window. the bathtub is gigantic and i was too impatient to fill it all the way up before i climbed into it, i kept the water flowing and i can feel it warming me, engulfing me. i think of all the tubs i‚Äôve floated in the past years, our own badtub in the appartment with the high ceilings but sadly no window in the bathroom. my tub in the attic apartment i lived in by myself that time we broke up those few month. it stood right under a sky light so i could watch the clouds drift by while i was floating in the foam, soft music drifting towards me from the bedroom. the gorgeous bathtub at my dad‚Äôs house that i spent as much time as possible in whenever i visit him. all the tubs in hotels and airbnbs, the way i not so sneakily always try to find a room with a bath when we go on a trip or a holiday\n\nwe booked this airbnb as a getaway, a space to breathe and retreat, on a whim. i just got back from another scan and the results wouldn‚Äôt be available for another week and decided we deserved a treat, time for us away from everything, my one condition was that it had to have a bath. the first evening there we go to the shop, buy all kinds of snacks and eat them in the evening sunshine. i am too tired to even think about a bath, the tension of the week of waiting and the not so great news have crawled into my bones and i crawl into bed after dinner and sleep 12hr straight. the next day i spent the whole evening in the water, feeling the air finally cool around us after a day of sweltering heat, a cup of tea in my hands and a glass of wine next to me. you are sitting in the other room, watching football, occasionally walking by to tell a story or to ask me if i want more wine. everything is still too much, i am still exhausted, but here in the water, i start to relax for the first time. exhaling just a little bit deeper, allowing myself to be carried. remembering the magic of water\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #soften #waterchild #mermaid #selfportrait #musings #healing #moonchild",
    "likes": 119,
