    "filename": "2022-09-09_2923583028292190864.jpg",
    "description": "when i first got diagnosed i cut off the whole spiritual/intuitive/magical/embodied part of myself and threw it all out. part of it was being so ill, not being able to do a lot of things let alone all the complex rituals and practices, i didn‚Äôt have the energy to find alternatives for them. part of it was anger and betrayal, the idea that i did all these things and i still got sick, so what‚Äôs the point\n\nit didn‚Äôt help that the selfcare world is a very ableist and unsafe space to be in. how do you heal in a space that keeps telling you that this is all probably your fault for not trying harder?! i hadn‚Äôt seen a lot of modelling of what it would be like to be here in a disabled body and frankly never had to find models like that because i could do it all\n\ni slowly made my way back to it though (or probably am still making my way back to it), realising that there are many more ways to be spiritual than i had previously seen, that there are safe space here too and most of all, that this is a part of me that i really want to connect back to. the past year i‚Äôve worked hard on getting that connection back, it didn‚Äôt look anything like what it looked like before but it feels more solid, more grounded than it ever was \n\n#spirituality #ableism #selfcare #healing #soften #tarot #herbalism #moonchild #spiritualityandcancer #chronicillness #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #soften #journal #rituals #sacredspace #embodied #cbd #signs",
    "likes": 120,
