    "post_id": "2937189891332001300",
    "filename": "2022-09-28_2937189891332001071.jpg",
    "description": "summer to autumn has always been the hardest shift on my system, physically and mentally. being incurably ill has only made that more complicated since it really does affect me more, the cold and the dark make it a lot harder for me to take care of my body and to stay positive. \n\ni don‚Äôt know if the shift was very abrupt this time or if i was in denial and was living in an endless summer kind of vibe but the past few weeks have been very hard and i am feeling so unsettled as a result (also, autumn is a very airy/vata/floaty season so feeling unbalanced or ungrounded right now makes a lot of sense energetically). i‚Äôve been floating around, keeping busy, feeling all sorts of cranky without looking at it too closely and today is the day i decided to pause and sit and assess the situation \n\ni‚Äôve been writing this morning, or really, i‚Äôve been reading a book and sending messages to a lot of people and distracting myself and writing in between all those things because sometimes that is the process that works. i‚Äôve been musings about what i miss, what i long for, what i need right now. and out of all that rolled this.\n\nmy manifesto for this season. my wish/intention/proclamation/incantation: this autumn i will allow myself to live in a way that nourishes me\n\nso simple, so hard. i‚Äôve made lists of all the things i love to do, all the things that inspire me. and i will lean into those things. a lot of it isn‚Äôt new or groundbreaking, in fact i think the only new thing on the list might be the painting with water colours which has been a plan for ages but it‚Äôs not something i ever actually did. the rest is a re invitation, of altar work and writing, of herbs and teas, of yoga, of tarot. leaning into the things that nourish me. today that looks like a cup of coffee with a lot of whipped cream in the sun. opening my journal after a month of barely any entries. baking a cake. some times grounding can be as simple as that, coming home after being adrift, making and eating good food, allowing in joy\n\n#autumnblues #sad #change #soften #nourishment #seaside #moonchild #cyclicalliving #slowlife #embodied #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurableillness #sacredspace #selfcare",
