    "post_id": "2941653183177713000",
    "filename": "2022-10-04_2941653183177713229.jpg",
    "description": "‚âò musings about unlearning, cyclical living and resistance |pt1 ‚âò \n\nthis is the pattern, my own circle of purgatory i can‚Äôt seem to escape from. i live a close to ‚Äúnormal‚Äù life and do all the things in a close to ‚Äúnormal‚Äù way and i convince myself of the fact that it is balanced and i am resting in between and i will be fine. then there is the crash, sometimes it‚Äôs after a day, sometimes after a week. my body is done with the too muchness of it all and reminds me of the fact that we are not 20 and we are not cancer free and this is not how we live our lives anymore. there is a lot of sleeping and scrolling. there are new books to read and cats that keep me company. depending on my mental state there is a little or a lot of feeling sorry for myself. sometimes it almost feels like a reprieve at first. after a few days i get bored and i want more and the first thing i always want is to write and then it can go two ways. \n\none option is me writing about all the things i want to do and the life i want to live and the fear that i will never be able to do it. it‚Äôs reflecting on how i‚Äôve been here for 2years and my all or nothing mentality is still screwing me over and how i haven‚Äôt found a sustainable way to do what i want to do because i am stubborn and i want to do things in a certain way, the prime example here is alway how i only want to write and scrap in a cosy spot with a cup of tea and that i can‚Äôt/won‚Äôt do it half awake on the couch. \n\nthe second option is me coming up with a plan and/or a list of a selfcare container to help me stay positive and sane. it‚Äôs a list of more movement and meditation and trying to find activities to do in bed that aren‚Äôt involving a screen. i‚Äôve written a version of said list/plan/manifesto a million times already. immediately after i‚Äôve written it i won‚Äôt to tear it out because it is too much pressure and ‚Äúhave to‚Äù lists don‚Äôt work well for me. \n\n||| continued in the next post |||\n\n#cyclicalliving #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurableillness #unlearning #soften #autumn #release #incurablecancer #shadowwork #musingsfromthevoid",
    "likes": 79,
    "comments": 3,
