    "post_id": "2944635899960510500",
    "filename": "2022-10-08_2944635899960510717.mp4",
    "description": "ìäì full moon ritual ìäì\n\nletting the moon and my body guide me. rituals can be found in anything. taking an extra nap and taking pain meds is ritual. adding rose elixir to my morning coffee is ritual. bringing back offerings from the garden. playing with flowers. sitting with my face in the sun. cuddling the cats. it‚Äôs all ritual, it‚Äôs all magic. \n\nfinding my way back to the moon and the cyclical has been somewhat of a process but i am having so much more fun with it than i used to have 5 years ago. before it was very much about the ‚Äúscience‚Äù of it, how it was supposed to be and feel. i put so much pressure on myself trying to find meaning while all of that has always been there already. now every moon phase is a gift, a chance to tune in, to ritualise the mundane, an opening for something bigger. \n\nfull moon helpers || smoke wand and rose elixir from @mirabellasbotanicals and north star flower remedy from @honeyhoneyhealing \n\n#fullmoonritual #soften #everythingisritual",
