    "filename": "2022-10-16_2950219666509745338.jpg",
    "description": "two years ago we woke up after a restless, sleepless night. i remember us holding hands and waiting for the sun to come up. i remember thinking this is the last morning that our lives are normal - even though in reality they had stopped being normal weeks ago, with the pain and the hospital visits and stays and tests. i remember how weird it was, that your life could feel so void, forfeit, that whatever would happen could depend so much on the words another person would say that afternoon\n\ni wore my favourite witchy dress because it gave me comfort and made me feel strong, but also because it was one of the only things that felt comfortable, being so bloated most of the time i couldn‚Äôt fit into any of my old pants. i put on red lipstick no one could see because of the masks but i knew i was wearing it and that was enough. little talismans. buffers. prayers.\n\n2 years ago today they told me i had cancer. stop the clock. stop life as it is. start the countdown.\n\n2 years ago i didn‚Äôt expect to be here today. but i am. so we celebrate. and we cry. and we pray some more. we live. \n\n#cancerversary #lifewithcancer #livinginthevoid #celebratinglife #incurableillness #bowelcancer #brafmutation #stage4needsmore #embodied #soften",
