    "filename": "2022-11-22_2977133753835928563.jpg",
    "description": "‚âò gentle reminder ‚âò\n\nwe are supposed to slow down right now. it‚Äôs getting darker and colder. everything around us is inviting us to be slower. softer.\n\neverything around us is inviting us to curl into the couch with a hot cup of tea and cosy blankets. to sleep more. rest more. do less.\n\nwe are animals after all. it‚Äôs only natural for us to take our cues from the seasons and the weather and the energy. it‚Äôs natural for us to wax and wane, to have moments of inspiration and creation and energy and moments of rest and nourishment and introspection. \n\nso if you have been feeling a little off, a little tired or grumpy or like you just want to curl up in a ball and take the afternoon to just sit here, know that that is only natural. that this means that you are in sync with the world in and around you. and if you are having a hard time allowing yourself the extra sleep and rest, you are feeling restless and like you should be doing more, know that that is also perfectly normal. that is what our brain and internalisation of our society is making us believe. again not something bad or wrong, something to be aware of.\n\nwhat if this season we allow ourselves to actually slow down?\n\nwhat if we see it as a way to move closer to our natural state\n\nas a deep rewilding and embodiment. as a sacred ritual. an invitation. a deep form of selfcare. a promise.\n\nwhat if this season we stop feeling guilty, we don‚Äôt resist and instead we lean into this? we allow ourselves to luxuriate in our rest, taking naps in the afternoon with the softest blankets and going to bed with a cup of lavender tea. searching for nourishment in the form of a new book or a new series. spending the whole sunday  afternoon on the couch with our loved ones. what if instead of feeling guilty about these things, we embrace them as the sacred ritual and homecoming that it is?\n\n#gentlereminder #slowdown #soften #embodiment #rest #healing #nourishment #oracle #leaningintorest #cyclicalliving #allowingourselvestorest #autumn #tarot #selfcare #journal #sacredspace #pillowfort #cosy #rewilding #livinginabody",
