    "filename": "2022-11-28_2981407407565825911.jpg",
    "description": "reminiscing and a little insta vs reality \n\nthe location was incredibly, magically gorgeous. it was my first time visiting zeeland and i completely fell in love driving through the landscape in the autumn sun, marvelling at the trees and all the water and we hadn‚Äôt even seen the sea yet by that point. the bnb was this gorgeous manor (which i called a castle in my mind) with deer running around the property, the room was an absolute dream and don‚Äôt even get me started on the bathtub. \n\ni was also dealing with  body that was struggling and praying that my digestion would start up again (it does that sometimes, not really work the way it is supposed to, it‚Äôs because of the scar tissue and the operations and the cancer) but this turned out to be a flu so i now know (still sitting in pjs recovering) that i hadn‚Äôt got a chance. i soldiered through on friday, going to the hotel as soon as possible to rest and enjoy the bath and each other‚Äôs company, hoping we would still be able to visit the sea and do some things the next day but overnight i only got worse and we had to leave saturday after breakfast (i didn‚Äôt have any but the hosts were so sweet and brought a whole table with delish things up for bram so he could stay with me while i was shivering and crying in bed)\n\nit‚Äôs the reality of planning things when you are chronically ill. there is all the planning and resting and hoping and praying but in the end there is always a chance our bodies won‚Äôt play ball and we won‚Äôt be able to do the things we want to do. it‚Äôs something i am learning to live with but also the thing that still hurts me most, being in the perfect spot with the perfect sunshine and the best company and not being able to enjoy it because i‚Äôm in pain or so exhausted. \n\non our drive back i was in so much pain and i was holding back tears and you held me hand and told me you enjoyed it anyway because we got to do it together and that‚Äôs very true. i am also still nourishing my soft little heart that is so sad for all the things i wanted but couldn‚Äôt \n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #instavsreality #travelgram #wanderer #mermaid #hotellife #visitzeeland #chronicillness #soften #embodied #sunrise #getaway",
    "likes": 143,
