    "description": "‚Äúdoes it sometimes bother you that you have to go to work everyday while get to sit her at home and watch tv and play with the cats?‚Äù\n\nas soon as the question is out i realise it had nothing to do with him and is something i have internalised somewhere, somehow. the swiftness of the answer makes it even more clear for me. because he sees that this is not a holiday or restful or restorative in any way. he realises that having to stay home and only having energy to put on a movie and nothing else is not a blessing but a curse.\n\nthese are stories i have picked up along the road, ever since i was born. takes that have been creeping under my skin for 31 years. that there is a good and a bad way to go about things. that your worth is derived from the things you do. that rest is something that should be earned.\n\ni had unpacked a lot of those things already, saw them for the lies that they are. and then the past 2 years came and i have been engulfed in it more than ever and i am working even harder on separating the facts from the stories, letting my reality and what that looks like sink in. god i would love to spend all day at home doing the things i love too, but truth is that‚Äôs not what i am doing. the caviat for that to be a joy is that it is only fun when it happens in a\nneutral body, one without pain or fatigue or restlessness. of course i have those days too but i guess people vastly overestimate how many neutral body days i get in a month, with the infusions and catching every cold there is, with the fatigue and the chronic pain, with the mental toll being incurably ill is taking. \n\ni am learning that rest is my day job now, that some days i like it and some days i despise it but however i feel about it won‚Äôt change the fact that that is what i have to do. i am learning to show myself grace here, in the midst of feeling not enough and lazy, that i can make things as cosy and as nourishing as possible and that it‚Äôs also important to feel the restlessness and the anger when i am derailed once again.\n\ni am learning to be here. if i would get a chance to choose i would pick going to work anytime over having to stay at home, being sick\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike",
