    "post_id": "3009198051861835000",
    "filename": "2023-01-05_3009198051861834713.mp4",
    "description": "we know this and still when it happens it comes as such a shock. life can change so fast. everything can shift so fast. even for a person like me who has everything upside down to begin with and knows that change is the only thing she can count on. \n\nin times of stability, we kind of forget.. thank god.. our bodies and brains and hearts can‚Äôt thrive in chaos, they can‚Äôt live in it. so somehow we learn how to live alongside it. alongside the pain and trauma and bad news. alongside hard truths and fatigue and grief. we kindle a fire of hope and beauty and gratitude and somehow - not because we are strong or brave, but because we are human - we live through it all\n\nthe contrast couldn‚Äôt be more huge, our england trip really felt like a rebirth for me, a reconnection to myself and my body and my energy. i felt awakened and inspired, like i had been granted some air after week after week of suffocation. and then the morning after we came home i had to go to the er and what i was sure would be a kidney stone wasn‚Äôt one and now everything is scary and on hold. i have an mri this weekend and then next week we‚Äôll know more. \n\nso here we are, hanging on again, trying to let the reality of the situation and our hope for it live next to each other. what i way to embark on our chariot year \n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurablebowelcancer #musingsfromthevoid #waitinggame #chariotyear",
    "likes": 69,
