    "post_id": "3018692709162326500",
    "filename": "2023-01-18_3018692709162326609.jpg",
    "description": "time is feeling very weird right now. it‚Äôs skipping and hopping, elongating in some spots and puddling together in others (im sure trauma + valium + anxiety meds are only contributing to it). some days i just know even at the moment that i wake up that i won‚Äôt really be awake, i doze and i sleep and i eat and i wait for the day to be over and then i feel guilty about that because i don‚Äôt have the luxury to just waste/will/sleep away days but there is not other option. it‚Äôs like my mind and body are setting the pace now and i imagine it does get a lot like this on our final weeks as well. it feels only natural to be in semi hibernation, that an afternoon is passed in the blink of an eye. only natural that this stage of the void comes with its own new particularities and tricks. it doesn‚Äôt help that its januari. that‚Äôs the first thing i said when we walked out of the oncology appointment where we discussed my therapy failing \n\n‚Äúbut it‚Äôs so cold and dark and empty, this time of year is like a black hole in even the best of circumstances i don‚Äôt know how i have to do stopping this therapy and waiting and praying for a place in a trial in this space‚Äù\n\nturns out this is the way, dipping toes even deeper into the total darkness of the void. learning more about timelessness. letting my body sleep for hours on end, with and without medical assistance. turns out, like every thing else, you just do it \n\n#musingsfromthevoid #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #bowelcancer #ptsd #trauma #timelessness #livinginthevoid #embodied #soften #hibernation #rest",
    "likes": 171,
