    "description": "the silence of this month tells the whole story, mostly. of one day bleeding into the next and the next and the next. of waiting and breathing. everything on hold. of living in a body that feels like a stranger, not safe enough to relax into. of letting things happen and no plans either way\n\nand now there is a glimmer of hope, and i know with my whole being that i am going to have to grasp it. work for it. lean into it. embody it. create alongside it.\n\nnow there is hope and it‚Äôs just enough to lift me out of this hibernation and into life\n\nhere‚Äôs to hoping the hoops i still have to jump through the next couple of weeks will be ones i can actually make it through. here‚Äôs to hoping this trial can offer another life line, another lease on life. here‚Äôs to hoping that my life still has to option to become more than it is right now\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurablecancer #bowelcancer #brafmutation #glimmersofhope #soften #hope #clinicaltrial #embodied #livinginabody #oracle",
