    "post_id": "3051296239924495000",
    "filename": "2023-03-04_3051296239924494800.jpg",
    "description": "it‚Äôs hard to remember this this season. especially this week. especially tonight. that this body can also hold joy and love and beauty and awe and nourishment. when all i can feel is discomfort and pain and dissociation.\n\nright now my body is more like a machine that doesn‚Äôt work properly, than a living, breathing slice of magic. so i work extra hard to find a piece of softness here, a bit of joy. that first sip of water after being without for a day. how soft this blanket feels. when the pain meds kick in and the pain is def not gone but the edges get blurred. the deepest craving for ice ice ice cold, thick milkshakes (preferably vanilla or chocolate) and the anticipation of getting one tomorrow.\n\nso in honour of my body being able to feel joy as well, here are my reminders in the form of photographs \n\n(also all of this is typed coming off on sedation after an operation to place a renal stent so stay with me if im not making much sense right now)\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurableillness #bowelcancer #soften #love #silverlinings #mermaidmode #dreams #cravings",
    "likes": 263,
    "comments": 38,
    "views": 0
