    "description": "england would be a tipping point for me, i know it before we left, from the point we booked the gorgeous appartement we would be staying in. i heard it in the cards and the whispers from my guides and the humming of my bones. and because i am a summer child and a firm believer in wonder and softness, it never even occurred to be it could be a tipping point straight to a new  rock bottom. 2 months and a half later rock bottom is the place i hang around most of the time, down and down at every turn. meds that aren‚Äôt working and new trial meds that aren‚Äôt so straight forward. lots of waiting and doing nothing. 2 hospital admissions and an infection and an operation. coming back home with a covid infection for good measure. new additions to this body that already needs so much help to function and what that does to my body image, what that means for the day to day of my life \n\nthis season has been about letting go more than i ever thought i could. losing more than i ever thought i could. the reality of life and how fragile it is, becoming very apparent, very much a part of the day to day\n\nit has been stable in an unsafe kind of way this week. yes i am home right now but somehow i don‚Äôt trust yet that i get to stay here. my mind doesn‚Äôt trust that i won‚Äôt be falling apart at the seams even more, that there aren‚Äôt other hidden trap doors\n\nthis one will take time, for my body and for my mind and for my soul. it feels like so long ago since i last sat down to write. whispered to my tarot cards. allowed myself to relax. all these things i want to offer up for myself that i am not quite ready for but i can hardly wait until i am. i can  hardly wait until things will get easier again, and i hope this time the tipping point will bring hope and faith and space with it. for now it‚Äôs resting, recuperating, building strength. waiting for spring just like i‚Äôm waiting for my body to be more solid and strong again. \n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #bowelcancer #uncurableillness #rockbottom #rest #intuitiveliving #cyclicalliving #soften #hope #tippingppoint",
