    "post_id": "3075602072691046400",
    "filename": "2023-04-07_3075602072691046364.jpg",
    "description": "the closer it comes, the more i realise that, despite what i told myself, letting go is going to be a messy experience for me (how did i even ever expect that to go any other way?)\n\ni somehow told myself the story that i was a letting go pro despite all the evidence in my life pointing to the contrary. what i am finding in return is flexibility of a kind. i‚Äôve been saying for months now that i won‚Äôt ever go back on chemo, that it might be for others but not for me again. i fought against it with all my might but now i ended up in the situation where it is the only thing i have left, after immuno failed and the trial isn‚Äôt having any effect and cancer is growing. my body feels like a mine field. my body doesn‚Äôt feel mine.\n\ni am so tired. bone tired. an exhausted that‚Äôs etched in the hollow under my eyes. tired of being in so much pain. of being able to do so little. tired enough that letting go seems like a legit and valid option at this point. somehow i am also planning on starting a new chemo regime next week..\n\ni don‚Äôt think that it‚Äôs brave or even that it speaks of hope. it speaks volumes of fear and too little time and too little good days. letting go is proving to be harder than i thought it would be yet i also knew that talking about this point and being at it would be two different things entirely. \n\nthese are real things and valid things and things we should talk about. sometimes i get these messages that tell me they ‚Äúwish me the strength to keep going‚Äù and then i always wonder, but who is going to offer me the strength and clarity to know when to let go?\n\nsometimes you just can‚Äôt keep going and that is real too, not quitting like some narratives would like us to believe. this whole post is a love letter to knowing when to let go and that sometimes the only thing more impossible than stopping is to continue on. so here is to holding on, and letting go\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurableillness #bowelcancer #braf #lettinggo #soften #folfiri",
