    "post_id": "3084363530602170400",
    "filename": "2023-04-19_3084363530602170162.jpg",
    "description": "there have been so many changes i have had to wrap my head around this last few weeks, it‚Äôs hard to even remember what life was like before it all started to go downhill very very fast. for the past few weeks i‚Äôve mostly been in survival/soldier on/fake it till you make it mode and there hasn‚Äôt been a lot of time to let things sink in or really take a moment to sit with all of it (also i desperately didn‚Äôt want to stand still). \n\nthings are kind of slowing down right now, a new reality is setting in and let me tell you i am having a very hard time with it. it doesn‚Äôt matter that i knew this would come at some point, somehow i am still baffled and confused as to how we got to this point.\n\ni feel hurt and lost and scared and angry and upset and numb and exhausted and annoyed. that‚Äôs a lot of feelings to handle let alone in a body that‚Äôs trying to digest it‚Äôs first chemo session.\n\npeople keep asking me if i‚Äôm okay and the short answer is ‚Äúi guess so‚Äù since i am here and breathing and taking care of myself as best as i know how. the long answer is.. complicated. i always thought there‚Äôd be more time. i‚Äôm feeling very lost in this new version of my body and my mind. i hardly recognise parts of myself and i am struggling to keep moving, to keep doing things because i keep questioning the why of it. \n\nthese past years i‚Äôve fought so hard to find a way to live a meaningful and soft life while sick and just when it felt i finally felt like i got the hang of it, things come crashing down again. i guess that‚Äôs life for you, right now it just feels like i‚Äôm in a crash course version of it and the waves aren‚Äôt letting up and i can‚Äôt help but wonder how i am going to carry all these things while it already felt so heavy, i already felt so exhausted. right now i really don‚Äôt see it and that okay as well, i‚Äôm taking time to feel all the feels and grief all the new losses\n\n(ps lots has shifted in this year so i made a little recap in the ‚Äúcancer update‚Äù story highlight in case you feel like you missed part of the story)\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurableillness #livinginthevoid #changes #towermoments #embodied #soften #bowelcancer #feelingitall #grief #chemolife #folfiri",
