    "filename": "2023-06-02_3116289931986979992.jpg",
    "description": "my body keeps shifting. changing. morphing.\n\nand i keep trying to find ways to feel okay in her. safe. embodied.\n\n‚çï\n\ni feel like i kind of glossed over the nephrostomy surgery, on here as well as in my actual life. it was one of the many things that has been going down this year, a small switch in this chain of decline. and at the same time it‚Äôs kind of a big shift, walking around with a tube that is coming out of your right lower bag, that connects to a bag that‚Äôs hanging in your upper leg and fills with urine. it‚Äôs not elegant in any way shape or form. i‚Äôm ‚Äúlucky‚Äù in a way that i had to get used to fistulas and ostomies the years before this because it kind of prepares you for your body becoming more machine like, less reliable. less sexy and pretty for sure\n\nsummer is coming up and it is baffling me. the past years i developed an ostomy friendly wardrobe. discovered that i like high waisted pants and underwear but not those ostomy bands that keep everything too close. that i still like to wear tight clothes and still can do that as long as the panties are the right ones. i even wear crop tops and a bikini in my garden, letting my ostomies out in the sun. i was all set and back to feeling some kind of confidence and now this year the rules have changed so much. \n\ni lost so much weight and there is no way of hiding it anymore. i buzzed off my hair. there is a bag hanging from my upper leg and it‚Äôs not trendy or nice (it is a white, fabricy kind of travesty that makes you wonder if any young people wear this at all). mind you that‚Äôs the ‚Äúsports‚Äù version of wearing a nefro, don‚Äôt even get me started on the lower leg bags because those don‚Äôt even allow me to wear any cute pants. so now i‚Äôm here, with all my short shorts and dresses because my legs were always healthy and okay and not screaming cancer to the world. and i‚Äôm unsure. i want to be able and strong enough to just walk around with it, covered up or not, but i‚Äôm not there yet. i‚Äôm trying to be, reclaiming it, step by step\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #bowelcancer #brafmutation #nephrostomy #ostomy #embodied #bodyimage #soften #livinginabody #folfiri #chemolife",
    "likes": 232,
    "comments": 29,
    "views": 0
