    "filename": "2023-06-09_3121301416655545290.jpg",
    "description": "what if there is still something importation to do here and..\n\ni don‚Äôt have enough time for it/i don‚Äôt get around to it/i am too paralysed to start doing it/i am too sick to finish it/i do it too late/i will never do it/i won‚Äôt be able to do it \n\nthese are the thoughts that keep me up at night. it‚Äôs a rotation, a sort of greatest hits that come around at the expected moment (scan time/bad news from (internet) friends/hard days/nice days). there are other themes that pop up but this is the most persistent one, maybe because it was something that was part of the rotation before i got sick? the question wether i was doing what i was supposed to be doing, pondering about change and life goals and purpose.\n\nit‚Äôs weird to be thinking about your death at 31. all of your peers are fully immersed in life, creating life and homes and families and careers. the way i feel right now is the crossroads of a quarter life crisis and mortality. it‚Äôs one of those themes i think wander around every 30something‚Äôs brain: am i doing what i am supposed to do in life, does my job/relationship/hobby bring me fulfilment/is this how i want to spent my time. i always firmly believed that life is meant to be lived, and there is no wrong way to do it. that we are supposed/allowed to try things out, make changes, make mistakes.. learning through living. i always considered our scars vital parts of ourselves, our detours valid paths. i always thought i‚Äôd have enough time to be a million different versions of me, no need to rush this one version of me into becoming the next one.\n\ni notice i still believe all these things, i just don‚Äôt have the luxury to believe that they apply to me. it‚Äôs a sad realisation that there are a million things i won‚Äôt get to try or do, that there are versions of myself i will never get to be. i notice how right now it mostly paralyses me and makes me not do anything. or maybe that‚Äôs really doing a lot, just living, without a plan, not trying to achieve something, allowing myself to just be.\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #livinginthevoid #quarterlifecrisis #slowlife #soften #purpose #creatrix #embodied #bowelcancer",
