    "description": "when we arrive at the kruidtuin another couple is taking wedding pictures inside the orangerie. i can see the gorgeous bride in her white dress. there are a lot of kids and groomsmen and various types of pictures that have to be set up. at the door it‚Äôs just the two of us and eva, just like it was two years ago, when youknowwhat was in full swing and it was miraculous we even got to take wedding photos at all. \n\ni put down my cane and my phone, put on my flower crown that‚Äôs still gorgeous after all that time. you put down my bag. you‚Äôve been carrying it for me ever since i got too weak to do that for myself and i am thanking you by making you walk around with a nijntje back pack all around leuven. you seem a bit nervous and don‚Äôt really meet my eyes but i know you don‚Äôt like your picture taken. \n\neva is setting up and testing the lighting while we ponder which shots we want to take, do we want them to be the same ones as on our wedding day? or maybe different ones? i don‚Äôt remember a lot of the shoot, went through it on automatic pilot with an achy hip, trying not to let too many thoughts slip in. trying not to look in your eyes too much because i can see those same thoughts reflected in them. \n\nwe‚Äôve both been coping differently, trying to give each other space to deal with things in our own ways. sometimes that looks like a lot of silence. sometimes that feels a lot like walking past each other, not next to each other. \n\npart of me was afraid to get those pictures in the mail, afraid that the confusion and distance was what would be obvious looking at  them. that it would be written in bold, how hard it‚Äôs been, how disconnected we can be, from ourselves, from the outside world, from each other. \n\ninstead when i look at these pictures, all i can see is the connection, the bittersweetness of this moment and how we are both carrying it. how we are  it‚Äôs carrying each other. the small cocoon of just the two of us in the world.\n\n#livinginthevoid #weddinganniversary #thisiswhatcancerlookslike #partnership #love #soften #mantelzorg #weddingphotography #coping #connection",
