    "description": "‚Äúdo you ever get a whiplash trying to keep up with my mental state?!‚Äù(part 2)\n\n(part 1 of this story can be read in the previous post)\n\njoy used to be so simple. i used to know/realise/feel that anticipation to something fun was actually the best part of an adventure, the planning and talking about it and bonding over it. now i refused to talk about our trip, except to say ‚Äúmaybe we should have a plan b, maybe we are really really stupid, what makes us think we can do this?!‚Äù i don‚Äôt want to jinx it and i definitely want to get all excited about it and then not being able to go because that‚Äôs a heartbreak i have felt too many times already \n\nby some sort of miracle though, we did it. we‚Äôve learned very early on when i got sick that we would never get out of the house unless we split up our plans into manageable bits (for both my body and soul). \n\nwe did the same for this trip: first mile stone was making it to the hotel, spending the night and having a nice breakfast and even if that was the only thing we could do, it would be a success. plan b was making it to the festival and seeing warpaint because that is the band i really wanted to see (and didn‚Äôt think i‚Äôd get a chance to see ever again in this life time). i think we eventually managed to make it to plan z: not only did we have a nice hotel stay, we went to the festival for 4 whole hours before i literally fell asleep on a chair in the middle of a crowd with loud music blasting. and then the day after we had a nice breakfast, cruised around antwerp with me in the wheelchair and we even had a kruidtuin picnic on our way back. so grateful we got to do all these things and my body did it with minimal complaining (and i didn‚Äôt poop my pant which is something i was actually very afraid of so extra win i guess).\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #livinginthevoid #accessiblejoy #soften #embodied #bowelcancer #wanderer #liveislivefestival #travelgram #chemolife #folfiri #wheelchair #smelltheroses #summer",
