    "description": "some glimmers of light and joy\n\nsometimes i have to actively remind myself that there is light here too. when it all starts to feel like it‚Äôs too much and too heavy and nothing is really working out for me. my brain (and i think i‚Äôm not mistaken if i say all of our brains) tend to focus on what there is most of, or on what is most urgent/vivid/present. in my life at the moment that is mostly pain and sadness. some days it feels like there is little, or even nothing, else. this is where this practice comes in, where i pick myself up and look through all the pictures and stories, or go outside in the garden, or read a nice book. this is where i actively go hunting for the good and the nice in the world (animal videos on insta are always a good place to start if you are reading is and don‚Äôt know where the hell you would even start to find these things).so here is a photo dump of all the good things these past weeks, the little glimmers of light in between the darkness and the sadness and the pain. the much needed reminder that life can still be beautiful. \n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #mentalhealth #soften #innerwork #embodied #thereisstilllighthere #bowelcancer #incurableillness #flowers #glimmersofhope #wonder #creatrix #tarot #journaling #scrapbook #bathtub #selfcare",
