    "filename": "2023-07-25_3154638434262528370.mp4",
    "description": "this is not something i would normally share or even take a video of. it‚Äôs very much a behind the scenes kind a thing and, thank god, for a long time used to happen so infrequently i didn‚Äôt  even consider sharing it. but today i have to. it‚Äôs starting to feel disingenious not to. to drop away from the face of the earth for days on end (here but also on messages with friends and family) and then come back with some random cat and food pics on a slightly better day only to completely disappear the next few days again\n\ni‚Äôve been off chemo for 6weeks on the dot now. i‚Äôve also never been as uncomfortable as i‚Äôve been these past few weeks. you‚Äôve heard me talk a about this before, the break i tried to give myself that turned into a mess and still it continues to be a mess. i can‚Äôt get comfy even in my fort with a hundred blankets and while taking all my meds and muscle relaxants and smothered in hot water bottles and while using a massage guns and having kine 2 times a week and using c.nnabis and the gravity blankets. im so overstimulated and angry all the time. my favourite part of the day is when i get to take a muscle relaxant at 8.30 and sleep a few uninterrupted hours. on top of this i got a UTI and the antibiotics i‚Äôm on for that aren‚Äôt agreeing with me at all\n\neverything feels too small and too much and too little and too overwhelming. last week i told someone i couldn‚Äôt even imagine what it‚Äôs like to not have pain every day, how it would be to live your life without constantly being at war with your body\n\nshe really has had enough now, she‚Äôs so tired and fragile and overrun. my head is much the same. i feel so stuck and alone and like there is little hope. i can‚Äôt even imagine doing chemo along with this so i keep pushing it back, cannot handle more. had a very nice app with my gp last week and am seeing my oncologist this afternoon and i really hope someone can help me feel just a  little bit less awful\n\nagain, praying for some space and rest and softness and hope\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurableillness #paindays #soften #bowelcancer #chemolife #folfiri #braf #chronicpain #spoonie",
