    "description": "when i say ‚Äúi wish there was more time‚Äù i mean:\n\ni wish there was more time where i feel good (or even neutral). i wish there is more time i get to spend doing things that light me up. with people i love. more time to dance and write and create and walk and take photos\n\nbasically, mostly more time but in a body that allows me to do all these things i love while it is not feeling too much pain and/or discomfort. quality vs quality had been on my mind from the very beginning, especially because i was so very sick when i first got diagnosed and i realised more time feeling like that would not bring me anything (and i know i can‚Äôt decided that for them but i also think it doesn‚Äôt bring a lot to my loved ones)\n\ntime isn‚Äôt the thing we want, not really, not when it boils down to it. we want the memories and the good times and the beauty and the love and the presence. the ability to be present in the moment. and i‚Äôve been missing a whole lot of that these days. a pain free, just a bit tired, grounded and embodied body is what i wish for most right now. some space, a little breather, as i keep calling it. but then every time my body tumbles and every time it gets a bit scarier because i don‚Äôt know if i‚Äôll be strong enough to pick it up this time. because i know at some point it will stumble and i want be able to catch it or help it back up and that is the scary thing. i can feel it creeping up on me with every bit of bad news.\n\nlast week i made a sort of joke, but actually it was the truest thing i said in a long time: when i pleaded with the god/goddesses/universe for one more summer, it seems i forgot the specify that i wanted a summer in a body that felt neutral (ish), being able to spent time doing the things i love. so i‚Äôll say it one more time, with feeling, and specificity this time, please dear gods/goddess/universe, i ask for (at least) one more nice, mellow, soft, pain free, embodied indian summer. it doesn‚Äôt have to be perfect, it doesn‚Äôt have to be dreamy and instagramable, just enough, and that doesn‚Äôt even sound like settling, that sounds like heaven.\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #incurablecancer #bowelcancer #eol #grounding #embodied #musingsfromthevoid",
    "likes": 308,
