    "post_id": "3202732420728979500",
    "filename": "2023-09-29_3202732420728979215.jpg",
    "description": "the moon is gorgeous tonight. trust me, if you  ever have the chance or urge to run out and have a good look at the gorgeousness that‚Äôs the moon, now is the time. you guys are gorgeous tonight with all the stories you are sharing and songs and words you are sending me ‚ô•Ô∏èno this doesn‚Äôt change a damn thing (a lot of you tell me this as well, but please know how much of a difference it does make to read these things, for me and for the people i love as well.  it s making my heart that much  softer and for that i am so so grateful.\n\ni haven‚Äôt really been feeling which i guess is the completely normal and correct reaction, since everything is going so fast and i don‚Äôt think i have ever made as many phonecalls in my life bc there are so many practical things to take care of. of course my nefro also got blocked twice today so i had to spent time at the er again which is awful but at the same time it also left me with this gorgeous meeting with the nurse that was there with me when i first got diagnosed and he talked about how i was one of those patients that will always stay with him and i think that‚Äôs beautiful in a way as well. also you sitting in  a chair, holding my hand, repeating over and over how you have my back, being my rock once again. don‚Äôt forget that there can still be beauty here \n\n#thisiswhatcancerlooklike #endoflifecare #palliativecare #musingsfromthevoid #moongazing #wonder cyclicalliving",
