    "description": "ìäì musings from the void || end of life edition ìäì\n\nthe medicalisation of my body and our home is happening at a stunning rate now. on thursday our house was still the way it has always been, i still went to the toilet by myself (without any oxygen), i even think i still showered last week. we started with camping in the living room bc i couldn‚Äôt make it up the stairs anymore. today we are camping in the garden room in a hospital bed, that i refuse to call anything but the garden bed. it is kind of cosy actually. our cabinet here has become a medical supply closet. every day i‚Äôve been needing the oxygen more and tonight was the first time i slept with it on.\n\nit‚Äôs a bit weird but it‚Äôs comforting for me to keep sharing these things (as always, as long as it feels good). it‚Äôs more the need to document this, to show that this is a huge part of life as well, and what that looks like exactly. also probably some need to shout into the void and assert y‚Äôall of my ‚Äúi al still here‚Äùness, always that of course too. \n\ni can feel myself being called to some of my old internet friends that i sadly already had to say goodbye to. connecting back to them and their stories. this knowing that there is a lineage of women that went before me, that are showing me the way and are waiting for me. allowing everyday to be whatever it is, allowing in beauty all around me however long it might be available.\n\n#thisiswhatcancerlookslike #endolifecare #musingsfromthevoid #soften #creatrix",
